data.title: 50 tips for improving your software development game
data.description:
Was reading about how to improve as a software developer, and found this interesting blog.
If you have questions like
*) What to do after learning basics of language?
*) Should we spend time on refactoring, testing? If yes then how much?
*) When it is ok to reinvent the wheel and when it is not?
*) How to deal with bad code?
Then read the following blog. It is a good resource to become better developer than yesterday.
Here is the link
